<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="AD2" checkit-title="Linear Approximation">
    <statement>
        <p>
Suppose the function <m>p(x)</m> satisfies
<m>p(9) = 89</m>, <m>p'(9) = 9</m>,
and <m>p''(x) &lt; 0</m> for <m>x</m>
values nearby <m>9</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
Explain and demonstrate
how to find the linearization <m>L(x)</m>
of <m>p(x)</m> at <m>x =9</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
Explain and demonstrate
how to estimate the value of <m>p(9.04)</m> using
this linearization.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
Explain why your estimate of
<m>p(9.04)</m>
is greater than or less than the actual value.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
Sketch a possible graph of <m>p(x)</m> and its linearization <m>L(x)</m> nearby <m>x =9</m>
to illustrate your findings.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
<m>L(x)=9 \, x + 8</m>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
<m>p(9.04) \approx 89.36</m>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
The estimate is greater than the actual value.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
